tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia and low creatinine, which may reflect reduced muscle mass or low protein intake, common in elderly individuals. Lipid profile reveals significantly elevated total and LDL cholesterol, increasing cardiovascular risk. Other parameters, including renal function, electrolytes, and microalbumin/creatinine ratio, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and consideration of lipid-lowering therapy.
